cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the use of Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs) and Case-Based Reasoning (CBR) systems in the context of eXplainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs), which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also touches upon the issue of human user evaluation, which falls under the sub-categories cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the XCBR problem, which falls under the sub-category cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
